OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1773850286
OL,3,CStarmer to face questions from MPs
OL,4,Cafter fresh Trump criticism
OL,6,FSpeaking on Tuesday, Mr Trump said he
OL,7,F"liked" the Prime Minister but felt
OL,8,F"disappointed" with his recent
OL,9,Fposition in regard to the conflict
OL,10,Fwith Iran.
OL,12,FAsked by reporters in the Oval Office
OL,13,Fwhether his relationship with Sir Keir
OL,14,Fhas been damaged by the UK's stance
OL,15,Fover the war in Iran, he said: "Well,
OL,16,Fhe hasn't been supportive, and I think
OL,17,Fit's a big mistake."
OL,19,FMr Trump then repeated his assertion
OL,20,Fthat "unfortunately Keir is no Winston
OL,21,FChurchill".
